23/11/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Senior officials took to the airwaves Friday (21 November) to reassure the public and the international community that the 2004 Olympics would be safe.
Speaking a day after the deadly blasts in Istanbul, Prime Minister Costas Simitis said that the government has taken "all the necessary measures to have an Olympic Games which are absolutely secure".
Foreign Ministry spokesman Panos Beglitis echoed his words, citing steps taken against international terrorism.
(Hellasnews, AFP - 22/11/03;
AFP - 21/11/03)
